{
  "texts": [
    "RQ2: What's the influence of chunking and prompting on the performance of the BPLLM?Table 2 reports the accuracy evaluated on different process model representations (natural text and BPMN) and different chunking techniques (no chunking, fixed-size, recursive, BPMN-specific).When natural text is used, similar results are obtained by relying on fixed chunking and recursive chunking.",
    "In both scenarios, the optimal chunk size is determined to be 128 tokens with a 10-token overlap.",
    "This finding can be attributed to the process model's relatively small size, with its content nearly included within a single chunk.",
    "This phenomenon also elucidates why the case of \"no chunking\" yields similar results.When the BPMN format is used, the results are quite different.",
    "However, a great difference in accuracy can be observed when different chunking models are employed."
  ]
}